question: Will Trudeau announce resignation by EoY?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if Justin Trudeau announces he has resigned, is resigning, or will resign from his position as Prime Minister of Canada by December 31, 2023, 11:59 PM ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

The primary resolution source for this market will be official announcements from Justin Trudeau or his official representative, however a consensus of credible reporting will also be used.

question: Will Travis Kelce and Taylor Swift break up by Nov 1?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce end their romantic relationship, or if it's confirmed that they were never in one, by November 1, 2023, 11:59 PM ET. Confirmation can come in various forms, including but not limited to, social media posts, interviews, press releases, official statements, or a consensus of credible reporting. This market will resolve to "No" otherwise.

If it's unclear whether or not they are in a romantic relationship, this market will resolve to the side with the stronger argument based on credible reporting.

question: Will Trump tweet again in 2023?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if @realDonaldTrump tweets again, between September 25, 12:00 PM ET and December 31, 11:59 PM ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

For the purposes of this market, all quote and reply tweets count toward a "Yes" resolution, but retweets will not count.

The resolution source for this market will be Donald J. Trump's verified Twitter account: https://twitter.com/realdonaldtrump.

Please note, only the @realDonaldTrump verified Twitter account counts for this market, regardless of the URL for this profile. If Donald J. Trump tweets from another account, it has no bearing on the resolution of this market.

question: Will Jadon Sancho play for Man United by Oct 7?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if Jadon Sancho plays in an official match for Manchester United between September 25, 2023 and October 7, 2023, after the day's relevant games have finished. An "official match" is defined as any official match in the Premier League, FA Cup, EFL Cup, or UEFA Champions League. The market will resolve immediately if Jadon Sancho plays in an official match for Manchester United before the expiry date. Playing in an official match is defined as taking the field during the official match duration, including extra time and penalties.

If Sancho has not played an official match for Manchester United by October 7, 2023, the market will resolve to "No".

question: Bitboy divorce by Oct 14?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if Ben ‘Bitboy’ Armstrong and/or his wife Bethany Armstrong announce that they are getting a divorce by October 14, 2023, 11:59 PM ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

For the purpose of this market, an announcement by either Ben, Bethany, or both, will be sufficient for a "Yes" resolution, regardless of whether the divorce later actually occurs, or whether the actual divorce occurs outside of the timeframe of this market.

The primary resolution source for this market will be official announcements by Ben and/or Bethany (these may be made via social media, e.g. https://twitter.com/BenArmstrongsX, https://www.instagram.com/bethanyreadsalot/, etc), or statements made on their behalf by their official and/or legal representatives. However, credible reporting from other sources of either of them saying they will get divorced may be used (i.e. Bethany shouts in a restaurant that she is divorcing Ben and footage of the encounter is leaked).

question: Will "Trump" be said by every candidate in the 2nd RNC primary debate?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if "Trump" or "trump" is said at least once by every participating candidate during the RNC primary debate scheduled for September 27, 2023. Otherwise, the market will resolve to "No."

Pluralization/possessive of the word will count toward the resolution of this market.

Mentions of the word trump need not specifically refer to any individual. For example if a candidate says "My policies trump his!" it will count.

The resolution source is live video of the debate. In case of ambiguity, an official transcript and/or a consensus of credible reporting may also be considered.

If this event is cancelled or delayed beyond October 27, 2023, 11:59 PM ET, this market will resolve to "No".

question: Will the final global heat increase be 1.15 or greater for 2023?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if the data for the Global Land-Ocean Temperature Index for 2023 shows an increase of 1.15°C or greater when it is released. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

An anomaly of 1.15°C or greater for 2023 will be sufficient to resolve this market to "Yes" immediately once the data becomes available regardless of whether the figure for 2023 is later revised.

The primary resolution source for this market will be the figure found in the table titled "Land-Ocean Temperature Index (C)" under the column "No_Smoothing" in the row "2023" (https://data.giss.nasa.gov/gistemp/graphs/graph_data/Global_Mean_Estimates_based_on_Land_and_Ocean_Data/graph.txt). If NASA's "Global Temperature Index" is rendered permanently unavailable, other information from NASA may be used. If no information for 2023 is provided by NASA by March 1, 2024, 11:59:59 PM ET, this market will resolve 50-50.
